# 3. アタシにできること

Shiho: Okay, let's end things here for today.
Honami: Nice work, everyone.
Saki: Great job! And it's sooo hot!
Ichika: Hehe. You were really giving it 110% today, Saki.
Honami: I thought so too. You made it so much fun to drum to your beat.
Saki: Hehe. That's because it's so much to play like this with everyone♪
Saki: (But still, I fell way behind everyone today in some spots...)
Saki: (That means I need to practice even more...!)
Shiho: Uh, Saki... After practice the other day, did you stay behind to keep working on your part?
Saki: Huh? Yeah, I did.
Saki: Even when we don't have practice together, I still try to play my synth as much as I can. Why do you ask?
Shiho: You just seemed a little tired is all. Are you sure you're feeling okay?
Saki: Yeah! I'm being careful like I said♪ I'm even taking fewer shifts at work because we're practicing so much.
Honami: That's good but try not to overdo it, okay? You're free to say so if things aren't alright.
Saki: I know♪ Thanks, Hona!
Ichika: We're also sharing the phrases we came up with after this, right?
Shiho: Right. I came up with some ideas, but how about the rest of you...?
Ichika: I have a couple. It was more of a challenge than I expected...
Saki: Oh! Oh! Me next! I came up with three!
Honami: That's amazing...! I could only come up with one.
Shiho: It's your first time, so one is more than plenty.
Saki: It'd be nice to have Miku and the others hear what we came up with too...
Ichika: Sure... But I am a little worried about having everyone hear something I made myself, so I'm sort of glad we're doing this today.
Shiho: Okay, and we can go in the same order as we did just now. I'll start.
Honami: That should be everything... So what did everyone think...?
Saki: I really liked Ichi's second one! The part when it switches to a minor key sounded so cool!
Honami: Me too. I thought it was cool too.
Ichika: Really? Thanks.
Ichika: Actually, I wasn't really sure what to do or where to go with that part...
Shiho: Maybe you tried to include too many things like you weren't sure which you should say yes or no to...?
Ichika: Oh, you might be right. I listened to quite a few songs as references and did get overloaded a little...
Honami: I see...
Shiho: Overall, I thought it sounded pretty good.
Ichika: Okay... But I feel like if we're going to be playing it together, there are better options out there.
Saki: Should we try a different one then?
Honami: A different one...? I had Shiho's first one as another candidate.
Shiho: About that... It's based on a song by an artist I've been heavily influenced by...
Shiho: It's sort of in the same boat as Ichika's. I'm not sure it's the best option for Leo/need...
Honami: Okay...
Ichika: It just seems even more difficult after actually putting pen to paper and listening to everything.
Ichika: It sounded alright when I was putting it together, but it's not what I thought it was anymore.
Honami: I agree... It's hard to say what's good or bad, so it doesn't feel right to make a judgment even after listening to everything.
Saki: Ugh... This is starting to make my head hurt...
Shiho: It might be because we don't know exactly what kind of music we want to play yet.
Ichika: The kind of music we want to play...
Honami: I never knew it was so hard to create a song from scratch...
Ichika: My thoughts exactly. Will we ever be able to...?
Saki: I think we will...!
Saki: As long as we're together, I'm sure we can! They say everybody goes through this in the beginning, right?
Shiho: Who's “they”?
Saki: Huh? Uh, well... I forgot...
Honami: Oh, Saki...
Shiho: It felt like the right thing to say.
Ichika: That's our Saki for you.
Saki: Hehe...
Shiho: But she's right. Nobody's expecting us to come up with something right off the bat, so there's no need to rush.
Shiho: It's going to take time for us to figure things out, so let's just keep trying...
Shiho: Someday, we will be able to compose our own songs.
Honami: Right!
Saki: Okay, see you tomorrow!
Saki: Hmm...
Saki: Our own original song. What would work best...?
Saki: (Hey, hold on a second...)
Saki: On a different note... Ichi, I came up with this tune while we were practicing. Want to hear it?
Ichika: An original tune? Sure.
Saki: Really? Yay! I'll play it now!
Saki: That's it...
Ichika: Huh, that's really neat.
Saki: You think so? Yay! You used to write song lyrics at one point, remember? Since then I've been composing little bits in my head every now and then!
Saki: (Right after we decided to form our band, I tried coming up with something and Ichi ended up really liking it...)
Saki: (That one part has a good flow to it too, and I'm glad we all got to play it together...)
Saki: (Wait, does this mean I can pull my weight by writing songs for us...?!)
Saki: (That's it! I might not be as good as everyone is when it comes to actually playing yet, so I can come up with music in the meantime!)
Saki: But what kind of music suits us best?! I can't figure that part out...!
Saki: I wish someone would give me a hint or something...
Saki: Hm? This song's...
Saki: Yeah, it is! It's that song STANDOUT played during that show!
Saki: That's so cool... It's really them on the big screen... This song and video are so amazing too...!
Saki: If only we could come up with a song like that...
Saki: Wait, I know!
Saki: (Oh, here it is! Just the CD I was looking for♪)
Shiho: Saki...? You came here too?
Saki: Oh, Shiho! Are you getting something too?
Shiho: Yeah. This band I like released a new single and I came to buy a copy...
Shiho: And you, Saki? That's a STANDOUT CD.
Saki: Hehe. Yup! I want to use it as a reference...
Saki: Oh, also! Are there any albums by your favorite bands that you recommend?
Shiho: Huh? Well...
Shiho: How about this...? It's a “best of” but it has songs from when they just debuted all the way up to their new stuff.
Shiho: These three songs here are among my absolute favorites.
Saki: Really?
Shiho: Yes. There was a time when I wasn't feeling too sure about myself, but listening to those songs made me feel so much better.
Saki: I never knew that...!
Saki: Then I'll get that too! I really want to listen to it now since you're willing to say so much about it♪
Shiho: Are you gonna use it as a reference too? That's awfully diligent of you...
Saki: Hehe. I want to learn about as much music as I can!
Saki: Huh? It's already this late...?! I'm gonna be late for my shift!
Saki: Sorry, Shiho! I'll see you tomorrow at school!
Shiho: Hey, wait...!
Shiho: She might be overdoing things again...
Saki: Hehe. I ended up getting two CDs. Now to check online for some videos♪
Saki: I'll start with STANDOUT!
Saki: STANDOUT songs have so much power behind them...
Saki: They really get the crowd going too, so that might be something I could try!
Saki: That one phrase had a nice flow to it, so I can sort of copy that and...
Saki: Okay, that should do it...
Saki: Let's keep listening to more songs and come up with more!
Saki: Phew. That makes six.
Saki: All these songs have given me so many good ideas...
Saki: What do I have left...?
Saki: Oh, that one song I heard during Tsukasa's show had a good melody to it too!
Saki: It might not work with a band like ours, but I can still learn something from it... Yeah!
Saki's Voice: Tsukasa! What was that song you guys used during that one show...?
